57 // The lexical analyser passes some information through to
58 // the parse store to be integrated with parse information before
59 // recording in the database.
60 inline void IncrementCount(LexicalCount tc)
61 {
62  assert(ParseStore::currentInstance()!=NULL);
63  ParseStore::currentInstance()->IncrementCount(tc);
64 }

66 inline void endOfLine(CLexer &lexer)
67 {
68  assert(ParseStore::currentInstance()!=NULL);
69  ParseStore::currentInstance()->endOfLine(lexer.line());
70  lexer.newline();
71  lexer.skip();
72 }

981 ANTLRTokenType CLexer::act130()
982 {
983 
984  // Check whether there are any dialect-specific rules
985  // about the current token.
986  std::string treatment =
987  CCCC_Options::dialectKeywordPolicy(parse_language,lextext());
988 
989  std::string toktext=lextext();
990  if( treatment == "ignore" )
991  {
992  skip();
993  }
994  // Ultimately, the next two cases will need to be handled
995  // using a #lexclass or something similar, for the moment
996  // we just try to skip the tokens themselves.
997  else if ( treatment == "start_skipping" )
998  {
999  skip();
1000  }
1001  else if ( treatment == "stop_skipping" )
1002  {
1003  skip();
1004  }
1005  return IDENTIFIER;
1006  }
